## System groups (do not create manually)

The bootstrap process creates and overwrites these on every startup:

| Group | ID derivation | Purpose |
|-------|---------------|---------|
| **Default** | `hashToUniqueId('group/default')` | All users are members; scope entries collected from modules via `CollectDefaultScopeValues` |
| **Permissions Admin** | `hashToUniqueId('group/permissions-admin')` | Highest scope value for every registered scope; grants full control |
| **Permissions Infra (×4)** | `hashToUniqueId('permissions-infra:<accessKey>')` | Document-level access groups for the permissions entities themselves (readers, writers, deleters, owners) |

System groups are managed by bootstrap only. Do not modify them from app-level code.

The first user to register is automatically promoted to Permissions Admin (one-shot). An RTDB flag (`grantAdminOnLogin`) provides a one-shot remote admin grant mechanism.

